    comment: '<p>Some characters are not easily typed on the keyboard, like the Copyright (©) character.</p>\n<p>To display the Copyright symbol, you can use either the HTML entity <em>number</em> or the entity <em>name</em>.</p>\n<p>HTML Entity Number: </p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x26;#169;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="54"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="54" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="33">©</tspan></text></g></svg></p>\n<p>HTML Entity Name:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x26;copy;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="54"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="54" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="33">©</tspan></text></g></svg></p>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;p>Copyright &#x26;copy;&#x3C;/p>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Result:</p>\n<p><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="320" height="54"><g fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><rect width="320" height="54" fill="#FFF" rx="9"/><text fill="#000" font-family="ArialMT, Arial" font-size="16"><tspan x="20" y="33">Copyright ©</tspan></text></g></svg></p>\n<!--[View CodePen](https://codepen.io/enkidevs/pen/WKRooB)-->\n<p>When using the Copyright symbol in your HTML, it is a best practice to use the corresponding HTML entity vs. cutting and pasting the symbol. Because  even if the symbol renders ok on your browser, it may not render the same on everyone\'s browser.</p>\n',
